ool which may not be experienced anytime soon. The way karmas are =\r\nassigned and ordered in these pools is based on the balancing of karma/karm=\r\naphala sequencing of all beings.\n=C2=A0\nThe assignment and ordering of thes=\r\ne pools will constantly undergo churn as one engages in various new actions=\r\n and adds them to the pools. Also, as new people enter one&#39;s life, possibil=\r\nities in terms of karmaphala delivery agents and sequencing may change and =\r\nhence the pools may be re-arranged.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nAs one en=\r\ngages in remedial measures such as prayers, fasting, donations etc, one may=\r\n transform one&#39;s nature, change one&#39;s vulnerabilities or re-arrange one&#39;s d=\r\nynamics with other beings (including planets, deities etc, who are the subt=\r\nle agents of delivery of karmaphala, who operate through other people who a=\r\nct as physical agents of delivery!). The karma pools may be re-arranged as =\r\na result. Some undesirable karmas may be downgraded to a lower pool or push=\r\ned down in order within the same pool. Or, some desirable karmas may be upg=\r\nraded to a higher pool or pushed up in order within the same pool.\n=C2=A0Wh=\r\nen someone curses or blesses one, with sufficient mental force behind it (t=\r\nhis is the key), the same thing can happen. It is all about re-arranging ka=\r\nrmas between the karmik pools. Every action by one, or even people around o=\r\nne, has the potential to re-arrange one&#39;s karmik pools. A karma about to gi=\r\nve karmaphala may be postponed or a karma that was not to give karmaphala a=\r\nnytime soon may be advanced sooner.\n=C2=A0\nHowever, remember that the remed=\r\nial measure has to be as intense as the karma that it is trying to manipula=\r\nte. You can move a small rock with small force, but you need a large force =\r\nto move a big rock or a hill.\n=C2=A0\n\nIf there is no negative karma in one&#39;=\r\ns pool that can give a specific result, nobody can make one experience that=\r\n result, no matter what ritual one does. However, even great souls have a l=\r\not of negative karmas in their optional pool and even evil people have a lo=\r\nt of positive karmas in their optional pool, and hence powerful remedies, c=\r\nurses and blessings can often make some difference.\n=C2=A0\nThis point is we=\r\nll illustrated by the &quot;Guru Charitra&quot; story Digamber ji referred in his poi=\r\nnt (3).\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nIf one thinks that one can escape the =\r\nfruits of one&#39;s actions, one is mistakened. God is not like us human beings=\r\n, who may show favoritism towards those who praise them or bribe them. The =\r\nHe-aspect of God is a witness to the play of actions and fruits. The She-as=\r\npect of God is the power that impartially and impassionately manages the fi=\r\nne balance and order within this play of actions and fruits. All beings are=\r\n equal in Her eyes, from the lowest of evil persons to the noblest of saint=\r\ns. She administers just and balanced delivery of fruits to actions using av=\r\nailable agents.\n=C2=A0\nThe karmas we committed in the past are already in t=\r\nhe pipeline and will give their results sooner or later. The best we can do=\r\n with them, with some effort, is to perhaps reorder them somewhat. The most=\r\n important thing is to not add more serious bad karmas to the pipeline now.=\r\n Simply put, selfish actions and actions that cause pain or harm to others =\r\nare bad karmas and selfless actions and actions that cause pleasure or bene=\r\nfit to others are good karmas.\n=C2=A0\nWhen it comes to manipulating the pre=\r\n-existing pipeline of karmas awaiting karmaphala, through conscious effort =\r\nand current action, yes, it is possible and general guidelines are availabl=\r\ne in shastras, but we can&#39;